main event: A civilian reported observing a round, white object, about the size of a silver dollar, on August 18, 1956.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes,The object was at about 90 degrees azimuth and 10 degrees elevation,The object was visually observed for 4 minutes before disappearing as the observer tried to get binoculars,The sighting was similar to a previous sighting reported on August 14, 1956,The source believed the object was the planet Venus shining through a temperature inversion.
